parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake caliper drag and lock-up can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially, accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels almost to the floor
making it difficult to stop the vehicle; the brakes get extremely hot; brake fluid boils out of the system; brake pads wear down excessively; ABS sensors melt; bearings are damaged.
